basics.name: Miguel Ocampo-Gooding
basics.label: Front End Developer
basics.summary:
I’m Miguel Ocampo-Gooding and I’m a front-end developer.
      I’m a huge fan of coffee and hockey. The things I’m focusing on right now
      in my career is learning about creating accessible websites for those with
      disabilities and working with Angular.js!  I’m going into my final year of
      IT at York University. When not studying, I freelance on whatever projects
      come my way. I’ve worked on projects large and small.  Outside of school
      and work, I’m the designer and webmaster for CUSEC 2016 and the Web
      developer for TedXYouthToronto 2016.

work.summary:
Developed and shipped websites and design work for a variety
      of clients ranging from startups to nationally recognized institutions.

Tasked with creating and maintaining a website for an
      international conference and designed promotional material.

volunteer.summary:
Led the design team to create sponsorship packages,
      conference booklets, posters, logo, and website.
